article.headline: Louisiana-Lafayette 73, McNeese St. 64
article.story: LAFAYETTE, La. -- Tyren Johnson scored 15 points to lead Louisiana-Lafayette to a 73-64 victory over McNeese State on Tuesday night. La'Ryan Gary scored 13 points, Travis Bureau had 12 points and Chris Gradnigo added 11 points to lead the Ragin' Cajuns (2-3). Kleon Penn led McNeese State (2-3) with 16 points and Diego Kapelan added 13 points. Louisiana-Lafayette shot 53.6 percent from the field (15 of 28) and 5 of 8 from the 3-point line to take a 42-30 halftime lead. The Ragin' Cajuns led by as many as 18 points in the second half.
